Key Match Events: Jayson Tatum scored 28 points, nine assists, six rebounds, and two steals in 30 minutes.
Tatum scored 26 points in the first half, giving Boston a 22-point advantage at halftime.
The lead expanded to as many as 37 points in the second half.
Boston won with a score of 123-93, marking their first 30-point victory of the season.
Post-Match Reflections: Tatum said he made the call to wear a headband, leading to a tradition between him and Derrick White.
White produced an all-around performance with 21 points, six assists, six rebounds, and two steals.
